What not to do

Avoid these traps:

Do not build a full engine first

You will get buried.

Use your engine as the demo/runtime, but make the company about the RL/world layer.

Do not start with humanoid robotics

Too hard, too slow, too research-heavy.

Start with drones, rovers, simple embodied agents.

Do not focus only on visuals

Pretty worlds are not enough.

The key is:

Can an agent act inside the world, receive observations, take actions, get rewards, and improve?

Do not pitch “metaverse”

Pitch:

simulation infrastructure for agentic 3D worlds.

Much stronger.

